<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="215" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="215">
<bibRefCitation author="Holzenthal, RW" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the New York Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="155 - 177" refId="B32" refString="Holzenthal, RW, Harris, SC, 1992. Hydroptilidae (Trichoptera) of Costa Rica: The genus Oxyethira Eaton. Journal of the New York Entomological Society 100: 155 - 177" title="Hydroptilidae (Trichoptera) of Costa Rica: The genus Oxyethira Eaton." volume="100" year="1992">
Holzenthal and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Harris’">Harris'</normalizedToken>
(1992)
</bibRefCitation>
description matches the specimens examined, except for the number of segments in the antennae (33 segments) in the specimens observed. Previously reported for the North and Southeast regions of Brazil 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.4.e8354" author="Takiya, DM" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 195" refId="B81" refString="Takiya, DM, Santos, APM, Pinto, AP, Henriques-Oliveira, AL, do Lago Carvalho, A, Sampaio, BHL, Clarkson, B, Moreira, FFF, Avelino-Capistrano, F, Goncalves, IC, Cordeiro, IRS, Camara, JT, Barbosa, JF, Souza, WRM, Rafael, JA, 2016. Aquatic Insects from the Caatinga: Checklists and diversity assessments of Ubajara (Ceara State) and Sete Cidades (Piaui State) National Parks, Northeastern Brazil. Biodiversity Data Journal 4: 1 - 195, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.4.e8354" title="Aquatic Insects from the Caatinga: Checklists and diversity assessments of Ubajara (Ceara State) and Sete Cidades (Piaui State) National Parks, Northeastern Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/BDJ.4.e8354" volume="4" year="2016">Takiya et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the presence of the species for the Northeast region, Caatinga domain (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ceará">Ceara</normalizedToken>
state) and 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4236.3.4" author="Souza, WRM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="484 - 506" refId="B75" refString="Souza, WRM, Santos, APM, 2017. Taxonomic study of the genus Oxyethira Eaton 1873 (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) from Northeast Brazil: Eleven new species and distributional records. Zootaxa 4236 (3): 484 - 506, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4236.3.4" title="Taxonomic study of the genus Oxyethira Eaton 1873 (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) from Northeast Brazil: Eleven new species and distributional records." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4236.3.4" volume="4236" year="2017">Souza and Santos (2017)</bibRefCitation>
extended the distribution for the Atlantic Forest and Cerrado domains (states of Alagoas, Bahia, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Maranhão">Maranhao</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraíba">Paraiba</normalizedToken>
, and Sergipe) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Brejo de Altitude de Bonito</emphasis>
(Pernambuco state).
</paragraph>
